column2: NA
1. Consists of social services, membership organizations, and miscellaneous professional
services.
2. Consists of (1) receipts by U.S. residents of dividends from foreign corporations, plus
(2) earnings distributed by unincorporated foreign affiliates to their U.S. parents.  Prior
to 1982, all earnings of unincorporated foreign affiliates were treated as distributed.
Reinvested earnings of unincorporated foreign affiliates were $1,571 million in 1982.
3. Consists of (1) payments by U.S. corporations of dividends to foreign residents, plus
(2) earnings distributed by unincorporated U.S. affiliates to their foreign parents.  Prior
to 1980, all earnings of unincorporated U.S. affiliates were treated as distributed.
Reinvested earnings of unincorporated U.S. affiliates were -$123 million in 1980,
-$163 million in 1981, and -$735 million in 1982.
Note.  Estimates in this table are based on the 1972 Standard Industrial Classification (SIC).
